Please be aware that we will not be supporting bash on the target and for licensing reasons we will be using ash.
ash does not support "function" keyword but both ash and bash will work if you omit the word i.e.

function start_swiapp(){

becomes

start_swiapp(){

better to improve the threshold for other cases. such as:
threshold = 1; when ecc_correctability < 4;
threshold = ecc_correctability - 2; when ecc_correctability >= 4.

This will tell the system to use UART2 as a console. However, it would be much more readable (we have multiple systems to touch) do the following:
* Define the following constants at the top of msm_serial_hs_lite.c file:
    #define CONSOLE_UART1    (0)
    #define CONSOLE_UART2    (1)
* Rewrite code to look like this (the purpose is to stand out):
    if((CONSOLE_UART2 == line) && (uart_func[CONSOLE_UART2] == BSUARTFUNC_INVALID))
    {
        uart_func[CONSOLE_UART2] = BSUARTFUNC_CONSOLE;
    }

Please, change text of this error message to more appropriate one. For example:

pr_err("Cooperative mode message marker is invalid. it is set to %d, but it should be %d", p1, p2);

You also need to print which marker failed to validate (you have two of them).

